The paper focuses on investigating the guidelines followed by developers in their projects related to exception handling in Java. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of exception handling code, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper touches upon code inspection and code review, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
